     **Bug[0m[2m 1:[0m[2m Overselling (inventory[0m[2m goes negative)**[0m[2m
     
     The `checkout`[0m[2m function has[0m[2m a TO[0m[2mCTOU (time[0m[2m-of-check-time[0m[2m-of-use[0m[2m) race condition.[0m[2m It[0m[2m does[0m[2m:
     1. `[0m[2mcheck_stock(quantity[0m[2m)` — reads[0m[2m `[0m[2mself._stock`[0m[2m with[0m[2m an[0m[2m `await asyncio.sleep[0m[2m(0.02[0m[2m)`[0m[2m 
     2. Later[0m[2m, `decrement[0m[2m(quantity)` — reads[0m[2m and modifies[0m[2m `self._stock[0m[2m` with another `[0m[2mawait asyncio.sleep([0m[2m0.02)[0m[2m`
     
     Between step[0m[2m 1 and step[0m[2m 3, other[0m[2m coroutines can also[0m[2m check[0m[2m stock and see[0m[2m the[0m[2m same available[0m[2m stock.[0m[2m 
     
     With[0m[2m 12 concurrent orders[0m[2m and only[0m[2m 5 items[0m[2m,[0m[2m multiple[0m[2m orders[0m[2m pass[0m[2m the stock check before[0m[2m any of them decrement[0m[2m, leading to overs[0m[2melling.[0m[2m Additionally[0m[2m, `check[0m[2m_stock` and `[0m[2mdecrement` both[0m[2m have[0m[2m `await` points[0m[2m that[0m[2m yield control[0m[2m, and[0m[2m the `_[0m[2mstock` field[0m[2m is modified without any[0m[2m synchronization—[0m[2msince[0m[2m `[0m[2masync[0m[2mio.sleep` yields[0m[2m to[0m[2m the event loop,[0m[2m the[0m[2m read[0m[2m-modify-write[0m[2m in `decrement[0m[2m` isn[0m[2m't atomic in[0m[2m the async[0m[2m sense[0m[2m,[0m[2m though in[0m[2m single[0m[2m-threaded asyncio[0m[2m the actual race[0m[2m happens between[0m[2m the check and decrement[0m[2m steps[0m[2m rather than within[0m[2m the decrement operation[0m[2m itself.
     
     The[0m[2m real problem[0m[2m is that `check[0m[2m_stock` allows[0m[2m multiple cor[0m[2moutines through[0m[2m before[0m[2m decrement[0m[2m runs[0m[2m, so[0m[2m I need to make[0m[2m stock[0m[2m reservation atomic[0m[2m. The[0m[2m simplest fix is[0m[2m adding[0m[2m a lock[0m[2m to `Inventory`[0m[2m and creating[0m[2m a `reserve`[0m[2m method that atomically[0m[2m checks and decrements[0m[2m.[0m[2m
     
     **[0m[2mBug 2:[0m[2m Ghost charges**[0m[2m
     
     Looking[0m[2m at the checkout[0m[2m flow, after[0m[2m a successful charge,[0m[2m `[0m[2mdecrement` can[0m[2m fail if[0m[2m another[0m[2m coroutine[0m[2m already took[0m[2m the stock between[0m[2m the check and decrement[0m[2m. When[0m[2m that[0m[2m happens, the function[0m[2m returns False[0m[2m with[0m[2m a message about[0m[2m a[0m[2m payment error, but[0m[2m the charge[0m[2m has[0m[2m already gone through—[0m[2mso the customer is[0m[2m charged but the order[0m[2m reports[0m[2m failure[0m[2m.
     
     The fix needs[0m[2m to handle this[0m[2m scenario[0m[2m where[0m[2m payment[0m[2m succeeds but inventory[0m[2m fails[0m[2m:[0m[2m either refund the charge[0m[2m or[0m[2m ensure inventory can[0m[2m't fail[0m[2m after payment[0m[2m succeeds[0m[2m. Using[0m[2m a[0m[2m `[0m[2mreserve` method with[0m[2m a lock solves[0m[2m this[0m[2m—if[0m[2m reservation succeeds before[0m[2m charging, the[0m[2m item[0m[2m is held[0m[2m so[0m[2m decrement[0m[2m can't fail;[0m[2m if reservation fails,[0m[2m we don't charge[0m[2m at all. This[0m[2m way every[0m[2m charge[0m[2m corresponds to a delivered[0m[2m item.
     
